observations.recommendation:
We recommended, and the Local Chief Executive (LCE) agreed to direct:

The Municipal Accountant to draw the necessary correcting entries in the Cash in Local Treasury account and reflect such adjustments to the affected Financial Statements, and ensure accuracy in the recording of collections and deposits as incorporated in the Report of Collections and Deposits (RCD);

The Acting Municipal Treasurer to submit the RCD to the Municipal Accountant within 10 days following the end of each reporting month;

The Acting Municipal Treasurer to submit the complete Bank Statement for all bank accounts to the Municipal Accountant for the proper verification of all deposits made; and

Implement frequent reconciliation of records between the accounting and the treasurer’s office.

We recommended and the LCE agreed to direct the:

Municipal Accountant to:

immediately prepare and submit the BRS for the eight (8) bank accounts, take up reconciling items, and prepare the necessary adjusting journal entries; 

regularly submit the mandatory financial reports and the supporting documents within the reglementary period;

Direct the Acting Municipal Treasurer to post the balances of the Cash in Bank- LCCA in the cashbook, with proper segregation of the sources of funds; and coordinate with the depository bank to ensure the prompt delivery of the monthly bank statements or its equivalent to facilitate the timely reconciliation of the Cash in Bank accounts; and

Provide the Accounting Unit with accounting proficient support staff to ensure that mandatory financial reports are submitted within the reglementary period.

We recommended that the LCE to direct the Municipal Human Resource Management Officer to: 

prepare the Organizational Structure and Staffing Pattern Plan in order to assess the required number of JO workers to be hired based on necessity and financial capability of the municipality;

ensure that all vacant positions under Plantilla should be filled up;

monitoring mechanism must be adopted in order to evaluate whether a JO worker is qualified for the renewal of contract.

We recommended, and the LCE agreed to direct:
The members of the local finance committee to reconcile their respective records and come up with a validated and revised LDRRM Fund Utilization Report and initiate actual transfer of the unspent portion of the CYs 2023 and 2024 LDRRMF;
The Municipal Accountant to prepare adjusting entries to correct the entries made in setting-up the unspent LDRRMF in CYs 2023 and 2024;
The Municipal Accountant to ask from the Municipal Treasurer the complete bank statements for the TF-DRRM bank account to properly record the transactions made from the fund and determine what year does the unrecorded bank balances pertains and provide details on the decrease of the Trust Liabilities- DRRM account;
The Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Budget Officer to initiate the reconciliation of records covering the periods CY 2021 to CY 2024 and should arrive at the correct balance of the unspent portion of the DRRM Fund and moving forward, to implement regular reconciliation particularly at year end; and
The Municipal Accountant to provide the correct disclosure of the LDRRMF in the Notes to Financial Statements.
Management accepted the audit observation without any reservations and agreed to comply accordingly.

We recommended, and the Local School Board (LSB) agreed to:
Prepare SEF Budget and ensure that all funds available including the prior year’s unexpended balance be included in the SEF Budget and provided with responsive and necessary PPAs, and ensure that all expenditures are included in the approved budget;
Furnish copy of the approved SEF Budget within 7 days from the date of its approval to the Municipal Accountant, Municipal Treasurer, and the Municipal Budget Officer and course through all disbursements in the SEF with the Municipal Budget Officer for proper monitoring and recording of disbursements;
Submit copy of the Annual and Quarterly SEF utilization report to the DepEd CO, through DepEd SDS and furnish copy of the reports to the Sangguniang Bayan and the Regional Offices of the DBM and DILG; and
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to ensure the accuracy of the quarterly utilization reports to be uploaded in the DILG FDPP website, duly validated and reconciled with the records of the Municipal Budget Office, and copy furnished the LSB and the audit team.
Management agreed with the audit recommendations and will comply accordingly.

We recommended that the LCE to direct the Municipal Human Resource Management Officer to: 

prepare the Organizational Structure and Staffing Pattern Plan in order to assess the required number of JO workers to be hired based on necessity and financial capability of the municipality;

ensure that all vacant positions under Plantilla should be filled up;

prepare a valid Job Order contract of service or Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) paid on a daily basis and period should not exceed 6 months; and 

monitoring mechanism must be adopted in order to evaluate whether a JO worker is qualified for the renewal of contract.

We recommended that the LCE ensure that:

(a) an approved travel order be secured first from the Office of the Provincial Governor or higher authority before the actual date of travel; 

(b) the corresponding itinerary of travel shall also be approved by the latter; 


(c) stop the actual reimbursement of meals and apply only the DTE as required by the E.O No. 77; and (d) submit the lacking documents.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive (LCE) agreed to direct:
The Municipal Accountant to draw the necessary correcting journal entries in the Cash-Local Treasury account and reflect such adjustments to the affected Financial Statements, and ensure accuracy in the recording of collections and deposits as incorporated in the Report of Collections and Deposits (RCD);
The Acting Municipal Treasurer to submit the RCD to the Municipal Accountant within 10 days following the end of each reporting month;
The Acting Municipal Treasurer to submit the complete Bank Statement for all bank accounts to the Municipal Accountant for the proper verification of all deposits made; and
Implement frequent reconciliation of records between the accounting and the treasurer’s office.
The Municipal Accountant and Acting Municipal Treasurer have acknowledged the audit observation and promised to act on the recommendations provided by the audit team.

We recommended that the LCE to direct the Municipal Accountant to:

Ensure that the correct balance should be brought forward as beginning balance of the Financial Liability;

Make correspondence with the Municipal Budget Officer for the immediate conduct of reconciliations between their respective records and every end of the month thereafter;

Booked up the liability to its proper and correct liability accounts and prepare the necessary adjusting journal entries; and 

 Ensure that all acknowledged obligations should be substantiated with relevant records or schedules.

We recommended that the LCE to direct:

the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Budget Officer to initiate the reconciliation of records covering the periods CY 2017 to CY 2022 and should arrive at the correct balance of the unspent portion of the DRRM Fund and moving forward, to implement regular reconciliation particularly at year end; 

the Municipal Accountant to:

Draw an adjusting journal entry to record the correct balance to the Trust Liabilities- Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund account

Maintain and update the related subsidiary ledgers and reports;

the Acting Municipal Treasurer to facilitate the actual transfer of the fund to its depository bank since the bank account was established for that purpose.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

require the Local Treasurer and Accountant to maintain property cards and property, plant and equipment ledger cards, and instigate the conduct of physical inventory of agency’s PPE;

direct all personnel concerned to prepare and maintain the necessary records and reports of Road Networks; 

execute the process of donation on purchased assets given to schools, and require the Local Accountant to drop from the books the related cost thereof; and 

direct the Local Accountant to make necessary correcting entries for the proper recognition of depreciation applicable to past and current years.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive (LCE) agreed to:
Direct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to quarterly reconcile the balance of Cash- Local Treasury account per GL and per Cashbook;
Require the Municipal Accountant to draw the necessary correcting entries in the Cash- Local Treasury account.

We recommended and the LCE agreed to:
Require the Municipal Accountant - Designate to:
Prepare JEV to correct the entries made on recording of partially completed water system project;
Prepare JEV to classify the completely delivered/ completed assets to its proper PPE accounts;
Ensure that depreciation is properly provided for each class of PPE as discussed in PAG3 of the IPSAS 17 and provide for the detailed schedule of depreciation;
Prepare the JEV to reclassify the PPEs amounting to ₱9,639,657.27 to appropriate accounts; and
Prepare and maintain property ledger cards and subsidiary ledgers of each PPE accounts.
Require the General Service Officer to prepare and maintain property cards for PPEs of the Municipality and effect regular reconciliation with the ledger cards of the Accounting Office.
Create an Inventory Committee, who are temporarily relieved of all their regular duties to complete the physical inventory in three months or less, and to prepare and submit the approved Physical Inventory Plan to the COA Audit Team at least ten calendar days before the scheduled start of inventory- taking activities and ensure full implementation of “One-time cleansing of PPE accounts” as provided for in COA Circular No. 2020-006.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) require the Municipal Accountant to: 

prepare the complete set of financial statements, trial balances, adjusting and closing journal entry vouchers, and books of original and final entries of the Municipality for CY 2020, and submit the same to COA for audit; 

henceforth, prepare the complete set of financial statements of the Municipality for succeeding years, and submit the same on or before February 14 of each year; 

duly prepare the monthly and quarterly pre-closing trial balances and timely submit the same not later than the 20th day after the end of the month; and 

prepare and maintain the books of original and final entries, and submit the same upon every submission of the trial balance.
